 RESIDENTS of Okuku in Odo-Otin Local Government Area, Osun State were thrown into confusion following the discovery of the body of a 55-year old woman, Afolabi Olawatoyin, murdered in her residence. The Nation learnt that Oluwatoyin was killed early on Wednesday. A source said the police have removed the remains of Oluwatoyin to Olanrewaju Medical Centre Mortuary. Police spokeswoman Mrs Yemisi Opalola confirmed the incident, stating that the officers have visited the scene of the crime and taken photographs. 